Single.Single: // The Heater function block controls the heating element behind the heat seal. It uses a simple ON-OFF logic.
// If the temperature is above the set point, the heater turns off. If it's below the low point it turns back on.
// There is a min and max temperature allowable for using the heat seal. If the temp is between these temps, it's
// okay to seal a bag. Outside of these temps throws various faults for the given conditions.
MinTemp: REAL; // Minimum allowable temperature for heat sealing.
LowPoint: REAL; // Low point. Heater turns on at this temp.
SetPoint: REAL; // Set point. Heater turns off at this temp.
MaxTemp: REAL; // Maximum allowable temperature for heat sealing.
Timeout: TIME; // Duration below min temp before low temp alarm.
TempOkay: BOOL; // Outputs TRUE if the temperature is between min and max temp allowed.
HighTempFault: BOOL; // Outputs TRUE if the temperature is above max temp allowed.
LowTempFault: BOOL; // Outputs TRUE if the temperature is below min temp past the timeout duration.
InvalidSettings: BOOL; // Outputs TRUE if the min, low, set, and max temps aren't in that order lowest to highest.
TimeBelowMinTemp: TIME; // Time spent below minimum temp.
